{"parse":{"title":"Ibn al-Wardi","pageid":16085270,"revid":829617768,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Ab\u016b \u1e24afs Zayn al-D\u012bn \u02bbUmar ibn al-Mu\u1e93affar Ibn al-Ward\u012b</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/Arabic_language\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Arabic language\">Arabic</a>: <span lang=\"ar\" dir=\"rtl\">\u0639\u0645\u0631 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0645\u0638\u0641\u0631 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0648\u0631\u062f\u064a</span>&#8206;),  known as <b>Ibn al-Wardi</b>, was an Arab historian AH 691 (1291/1292)-AH 749 (1348/1349), the author of <i>Khar\u012bdat al-\u02bfAj\u0101'ib wa far\u012bdat al-gha'r\u0101ib</i> (\"The Pearl of wonders and the Uniqueness of strange things\"), a geographical treatise with sections on natural history.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ency-islam-ibn_al-Wardi_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ency-islam-ibn_al-Wardi-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> He also wrote <i>Tarikh Ibn al-Wardi</i> (\"The History by Ibn al-Wardi\").\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Kharidat\">Kharidat</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ibn_al-Wardi&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Kharidat\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Ibn_al_Wardi%27s_atlas.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d3/Ibn_al_Wardi%27s_atlas.jpg/220px-Ibn_al_Wardi%27s_atlas.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"147\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d3/Ibn_al_Wardi%27s_atlas.jpg/330px-Ibn_al_Wardi%27s_atlas.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d3/Ibn_al_Wardi%27s_atlas.jpg/440px-Ibn_al_Wardi%27s_atlas.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"640\" data-file-height=\"429\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Ibn_al_Wardi%27s_atlas.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Ibn al-Wardi's atlas of the world, a manuscript copied in 17th century</div></div></div>\n<p>The <i>Khar\u012bdat</i> summed up the geographical knowledge of the Arabic world of the time, referring to climate, terrain, fauna and flora, population, way of living, existing states and their governments in individual regions of the world. The work was accompanied by a coloured world map and a picture of Ka'bah.\n</p><p>Although in the book al-Wardi credits <a href=\"/wiki/Al-Mas%27udi\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Al-Mas&#39;udi\">al-Mas'udi</a>, <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=A%E1%B8%A5mad_al_%E1%B9%AC%C5%ABs%C4%AB&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"A\u1e25mad al \u1e6c\u016bs\u012b (page does not exist)\">al-Tusi</a> and several other sources, <a href=\"/wiki/Mohamed_Bencheneb\" title=\"Mohamed Bencheneb\">Mohamed Bencheneb</a> claimed it was merely a plagiarism of a book by Egyptian writer Najm ad-D\u012bn A\u1e25mad ibn \u1e24amd\u0101n ibn Shabib al-\u1e24anbali (ca. 1332), entitled <i>J\u0101mi \u02bfal-Fun\u016bn wa-Salwat al-Ma\u1e25z\u016bn</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-ency-islam-ibn_al-Wardi_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ency-islam-ibn_al-Wardi-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> As for the first chapter of the <i>Kharidat</i>, although it may have well come indirectly through al-\u1e24anbali as Bencheneb suggests, it is in fact very nearly a copy from <a href=\"/wiki/Yaqut_al-Hamawi\" title=\"Yaqut al-Hamawi\">Yaqut</a>'s <i><a href=\"/wiki/Mu%27jam_al-Buldan\" title=\"Mu&#39;jam al-Buldan\">Mu'jam ul-Buld\u0101n</a></i>, including similar phraseology.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The author also speaks about Slavs and their lifestyle and mentions al-Mahdiyya as the residence of the Fatimid dynasty. Therefore, the book is older than the city of Kairo (founded in 969 C. E.).  \n</p><p><br />\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ibn_al-Wardi&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<dl><dt>Citations</dt></dl>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-ency-islam-ibn_al-Wardi-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-ency-islam-ibn_al-Wardi_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-ency-islam-ibn_al-Wardi_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<cite id=\"CITEREFBencheneb1936\" class=\"citation\"><a href=\"/wiki/Mohamed_Bencheneb\" title=\"Mohamed Bencheneb\">Bencheneb, Mohamed</a> (1936), <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=xd5VonTOppMC&amp;pg=PA428)\">\"Ibn al-Ward\u012b\"</a>, <i>The Encyclopaedia of Isl\u0101m</i>, E. J. Brill ltd., <b>III</b>, p.&#160;428</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Encyclopaedia+of+Isl%C4%81m&amp;rft.atitle=Ibn+al-Ward%C4%AB&amp;rft.volume=III&amp;rft.pages=428&amp;rft.date=1936&amp;rft.aulast=Bencheneb&amp;rft.aufirst=Mohamed&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3Dxd5VonTOppMC%26pg%3DPA428%29&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIbn+al-Wardi\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFJwaideh1987\">Jwaideh (1987)</a>, p. 19, note 4.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFJwaideh1987\">Jwaideh (1987)</a>, p. 19, note 4.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<dl><dt>Bibliography</dt></dl>\n<ul><li><cite id=\"CITEREFJwaideh1987\" class=\"citation book\">Jwaideh, Wadie, ed. (1987) [1959]. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=a_8UAAAAIAAJ&amp;pg=PA34\"><i>The Introductory Chapters of Y\u0101q\u016bt's Mu\u02bbjam Al-Buld\u0101n</i></a>. Brill Archive.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Introductory+Chapters+of+Y%C4%81q%C5%ABt%27s+Mu%CA%BBjam+Al-Buld%C4%81n&amp;rft.pub=Brill+Archive&amp;rft.date=1987&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3Da_8UAAAAIAAJ%26pg%3DPA34&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIbn+al-Wardi\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li></ul>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ibn_al-Wardi&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://portal.unesco.org/ci/en/ev.php-URL_ID=17261&amp;URL_DO=DO_TOPIC&amp;URL_SECTION=201.html\">http://portal.unesco.org/ci/en/ev.php-URL_ID=17261&amp;URL_DO=DO_TOPIC&amp;URL_SECTION=201.html</a></li></ul>\n<div role=\"navigation\" class=\"navbox\" aria-labelledby=\"Authority_control_frameless_&amp;#124;text-top_&amp;#124;10px_&amp;#124;alt=Edit_this_at_Wikidata_&amp;#124;link=https&amp;#58;//www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q5984319&amp;#124;Edit_this_at_Wikidata\" style=\"padding:3px\"><table class=\"nowraplinks hl